{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So, I want to start out with"},{"time":2000,"text":"this beautiful picture from my childhood."},{"time":4000,"text":"I love the science fiction movies."},{"time":6000,"text":"Here it is: \"This Island Earth.\""},{"time":8000,"text":"And leave it to Hollywood to get it just right."},{"time":10000,"text":"Two-and-a-half years in the making."},{"time":12000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":15000,"text":"I mean, even the creationists give us 6,000,"},{"time":18000,"text":"but Hollywood goes to the chase."},{"time":20000,"text":"And in this movie, we see what we think is out there:"},{"time":24000,"text":"flying saucers and aliens."},{"time":27000,"text":"Every world has an alien, and every alien world has a flying saucer,"},{"time":30000,"text":"and they move about with great speed. Aliens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"Well, Don Brownlee, my friend, and I finally got to the point"},{"time":38000,"text":"where we got tired of turning on the TV"},{"time":41000,"text":"and seeing the spaceships and seeing the aliens every night,"},{"time":44000,"text":"and tried to write a counter-argument to it,"},{"time":47000,"text":"and put out what does it really take for an Earth to be habitable,"},{"time":51000,"text":"for a planet to be an Earth, to have a place"},{"time":53000,"text":"where you could probably get not just life, but complexity,"},{"time":56000,"text":"which requires a huge amount of evolution,"},{"time":58000,"text":"and therefore constancy of conditions."},{"time":61000,"text":"So, in 2000 we wrote \"Rare Earth.\" In 2003, we then asked,"},{"time":64000,"text":"let's not think about where Earths are in space, but how long has Earth been Earth?"},{"time":69000,"text":"If you go back two billion years,"},{"time":71000,"text":"you're not on an Earth-like planet any more."},{"time":73000,"text":"What we call an Earth-like planet is actually a very short interval of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77000,"text":"Well, \"Rare Earth\" actually"},{"time":79000,"text":"taught me an awful lot about meeting the public."},{"time":82000,"text":"Right after, I got an invitation to go to a science fiction convention,"},{"time":85000,"text":"and with all great earnestness walked in."},{"time":88000,"text":"David Brin was going to debate me on this,"},{"time":90000,"text":"and as I walked in, the crowd of a hundred started booing lustily."},{"time":94000,"text":"I had a girl who came up who said, \"My dad says you're the devil.\""},{"time":97000,"text":"You cannot take people's aliens away from them"},{"time":101000,"text":"and expect to be anybody's friends."},{"time":105000,"text":"Well, the second part of that, soon after --"},{"time":107000,"text":"and I was talking to Paul Allen; I saw him in the audience,"},{"time":110000,"text":"and I handed him a copy of \"Rare Earth.\""},{"time":112000,"text":"And Jill Tarter was there, and she turned to me,"},{"time":116000,"text":"and she looked at me just like that girl in \"The Exorcist.\""},{"time":119000,"text":"It was, \"It burns! It burns!\""},{"time":121000,"text":"Because SETI doesn't want to hear this."},{"time":123000,"text":"SETI wants there to be stuff out there."},{"time":126000,"text":"I really applaud the SETI efforts, but we have not heard anything yet."},{"time":129000,"text":"And I really do think we have to start thinking"},{"time":131000,"text":"about what's a good planet and what isn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134000,"text":"Now, I throw this slide up because it indicates to me that,"},{"time":137000,"text":"even if SETI does hear something, can we figure out what they said?"},{"time":141000,"text":"Because this was a slide that was passed"},{"time":143000,"text":"between the two major intelligences on Earth -- a Mac to a PC --"},{"time":147000,"text":"and it can't even get the letters right --"},{"time":150000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":152000,"text":"-- so how are we going to talk to the aliens?"},{"time":154000,"text":"And if they're 50 light years away, and we call them up,"},{"time":157000,"text":"and you blah, blah, blah, blah, blah,"},{"time":159000,"text":"and then 50 years later it comes back and they say, Please repeat?"},{"time":162000,"text":"I mean, there we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164000,"text":"Our planet is a good planet because it can keep water."},{"time":167000,"text":"Mars is a bad planet, but it's still good enough for us to go there"},{"time":171000,"text":"and to live on its surface if we're protected."},{"time":173000,"text":"But Venus is a very bad -- the worst -- planet."},{"time":176000,"text":"Even though it's Earth-like, and even though early in its history"},{"time":179000,"text":"it may very well have harbored Earth-like life,"},{"time":182000,"text":"it soon succumbed to runaway greenhouse --"},{"time":185000,"text":"that's an 800 degrees [Fahrenheit] surface --"},{"time":187000,"text":"because of rampant carbon dioxide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"Well, we know from astrobiology that we can really now predict"},{"time":193000,"text":"what's going to happen to our particular planet."},{"time":196000,"text":"We are right now in the beautiful Oreo"},{"time":199000,"text":"of existence -- of at least life on Planet Earth --"},{"time":202000,"text":"following the first horrible microbial age."},{"time":205000,"text":"In the Cambrian explosion, life emerged from the swamps,"},{"time":208000,"text":"complexity arose,"},{"time":210000,"text":"and from what we can tell, we're halfway through."},{"time":213000,"text":"We have as much time for animals to exist on this planet"},{"time":216000,"text":"as they have been here now,"},{"time":218000,"text":"till we hit the second microbial age."},{"time":220000,"text":"And that will happen, paradoxically --"},{"time":222000,"text":"everything you hear about global warming --"},{"time":224000,"text":"when we hit CO2 down to 10 parts per million,"},{"time":227000,"text":"we are no longer going to have to have plants"},{"time":229000,"text":"that are allowed to have any photosynthesis, and there go animals."},{"time":233000,"text":"So, after that we probably have seven billion years."},{"time":235000,"text":"The Sun increases in its intensity, in its brightness,"},{"time":238000,"text":"and finally, at about 12 billion years after it first started,"},{"time":243000,"text":"the Earth is consumed by a large Sun,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and this is what's left."},{"time":249000,"text":"So, a planet like us is going to have an age and an old age,"},{"time":253000,"text":"and we are in its golden summer age right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257000,"text":"But there's two fates to everything, isn't there?"},{"time":259000,"text":"Now, a lot of you are going to die of old age,"},{"time":262000,"text":"but some of you, horribly enough, are going to die in an accident."},{"time":265000,"text":"And that's the fate of a planet, too."},{"time":267000,"text":"Earth, if we're lucky enough -- if it doesn't get hit by a Hale-Bopp,"},{"time":271000,"text":"or gets blasted by some supernova nearby"},{"time":275000,"text":"in the next seven billion years -- we'll find under your feet."},{"time":278000,"text":"But what about accidental death?"},{"time":280000,"text":"Well, paleontologists for the last 200 years"},{"time":282000,"text":"have been charting death. It's strange --"},{"time":284000,"text":"extinction as a concept wasn't even thought about"},{"time":287000,"text":"until Baron Cuvier in France found this first mastodon."},{"time":290000,"text":"He couldn't match it up to any bones on the planet,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and he said, Aha! It's extinct."},{"time":294000,"text":"And very soon after, the fossil record started yielding"},{"time":297000,"text":"a very good idea of how many plants and animals there have been"},{"time":300000,"text":"since complex life really began to leave"},{"time":302000,"text":"a very interesting fossil record."},{"time":305000,"text":"In that complex record of fossils,"},{"time":308000,"text":"there were times when lots of stuff"},{"time":310000,"text":"seemed to be dying out very quickly,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and the father/mother geologists"},{"time":314000,"text":"called these \"mass extinctions.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":316000,"text":"All along it was thought to be either an act of God"},{"time":318000,"text":"or perhaps long, slow climate change, \n"},{"time":320000,"text":"and that really changed in 1980,"},{"time":322000,"text":"in this rocky outcrop near Gubbio,"},{"time":325000,"text":"where Walter Alvarez, trying to figure out"},{"time":328000,"text":"what was the time difference between these white rocks,"},{"time":331000,"text":"which held creatures of the Cretaceous period,"},{"time":333000,"text":"and the pink rocks above, which held Tertiary fossils."},{"time":335000,"text":"How long did it take to go from one system to the next?"},{"time":339000,"text":"And what they found was something unexpected."},{"time":341000,"text":"They found in this gap, in between, a very thin clay layer,"},{"time":344000,"text":"and that clay layer -- this very thin red layer here --"},{"time":347000,"text":"is filled with iridium."},{"time":349000,"text":"And not just iridium; it's filled with glassy spherules,"},{"time":352000,"text":"and it's filled with quartz grains"},{"time":354000,"text":"that have been subjected to enormous pressure: shock quartz."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"Now, in this slide the white is chalk,"},{"time":360000,"text":"and this chalk was deposited in a warm ocean."},{"time":363000,"text":"The chalk itself's composed by plankton"},{"time":365000,"text":"which has fallen down from the sea surface onto the sea floor,"},{"time":369000,"text":"so that 90 percent of the sediment here is skeleton of living stuff,"},{"time":372000,"text":"and then you have that millimeter-thick red layer,"},{"time":374000,"text":"and then you have black rock."},{"time":376000,"text":"And the black rock is the sediment on the sea bottom"},{"time":379000,"text":"in the absence of plankton."},{"time":381000,"text":"And that's what happens in an asteroid catastrophe,"},{"time":385000,"text":"because that's what this was, of course. This is the famous K-T."},{"time":388000,"text":"A 10-kilometer body hit the planet."},{"time":390000,"text":"The effects of it spread this very thin impact layer all over the planet,"},{"time":394000,"text":"and we had very quickly the death of the dinosaurs,"},{"time":397000,"text":"the death of these beautiful ammonites,"},{"time":399000,"text":"Leconteiceras here, and Celaeceras over here,"},{"time":401000,"text":"and so much else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403000,"text":"I mean, it must be true,"},{"time":405000,"text":"because we've had two Hollywood blockbusters since that time,"},{"time":408000,"text":"and this paradigm, from 1980 to about 2000,"},{"time":411000,"text":"totally changed how we geologists thought about catastrophes."},{"time":416000,"text":"Prior to that, uniformitarianism was the dominant paradigm:"},{"time":419000,"text":"the fact that if anything happens on the planet in the past,"},{"time":422000,"text":"there are present-day processes that will explain it."},{"time":426000,"text":"But we haven't witnessed a big asteroid impact,"},{"time":429000,"text":"so this is a type of neo-catastrophism,"},{"time":431000,"text":"and it took about 20 years for the scientific establishment"},{"time":434000,"text":"to finally come to grips: yes, we were hit;"},{"time":436000,"text":"and yes, the effects of that hit caused a major mass extinction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441000,"text":"Well, there are five major mass extinctions \n"},{"time":443000,"text":"over the last 500 million years, called the Big Five."},{"time":446000,"text":"They range from 450 million years ago"},{"time":449000,"text":"to the last, the K-T, number four,"},{"time":451000,"text":"but the biggest of all was the P, or the Permian extinction,"},{"time":455000,"text":"sometimes called the mother of all mass extinctions."},{"time":457000,"text":"And every one of these has been subsequently blamed"},{"time":460000,"text":"on large-body impact."},{"time":462000,"text":"But is this true?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":465000,"text":"The most recent, the Permian, was thought to have been an impact"},{"time":468000,"text":"because of this beautiful structure on the right."},{"time":470000,"text":"This is a Buckminsterfullerene, a carbon-60."},{"time":473000,"text":"Because it looks like those terrible geodesic domes"},{"time":476000,"text":"of my late beloved '60s,"},{"time":478000,"text":"they're called \"buckyballs.\""},{"time":480000,"text":"This evidence was used to suggest"},{"time":482000,"text":"that at the end of the Permian, 250 million years ago, a comet hit us."},{"time":486000,"text":"And when the comet hits, the pressure produces the buckyballs,"},{"time":489000,"text":"and it captures bits of the comet."},{"time":491000,"text":"Helium-3: very rare on the surface of the Earth, very common in space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496000,"text":"But is this true?"},{"time":498000,"text":"In 1990, working on the K-T extinction for 10 years,"},{"time":502000,"text":"I moved to South Africa to begin work twice a year"},{"time":505000,"text":"in the great Karoo desert."},{"time":507000,"text":"I was so lucky to watch the change of that South Africa"},{"time":510000,"text":"into the new South Africa as I went year by year."},{"time":513000,"text":"And I worked on this Permian extinction,"},{"time":515000,"text":"camping by this Boer graveyard for months at a time."},{"time":518000,"text":"And the fossils are extraordinary."},{"time":521000,"text":"You know, you're gazing upon your very distant ancestors."},{"time":523000,"text":"These are mammal-like reptiles."},{"time":525000,"text":"They are culturally invisible. We do not make movies about these."},{"time":528000,"text":"This is a Gorgonopsian, or a Gorgon."},{"time":530000,"text":"That's an 18-inch long skull of an animal"},{"time":534000,"text":"that was probably seven or eight feet, sprawled like a lizard,"},{"time":538000,"text":"probably had a head like a lion."},{"time":540000,"text":"This is the top carnivore, the T-Rex of its time."},{"time":542000,"text":"But there's lots of stuff."},{"time":544000,"text":"This is my poor son, Patrick."},{"time":546000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":547000,"text":"This is called paleontological child abuse."},{"time":550000,"text":"Hold still, you're the scale."},{"time":552000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":558000,"text":"There was big stuff back then."},{"time":561000,"text":"Fifty-five species of mammal-like reptiles."},{"time":564000,"text":"The age of mammals had well and truly started"},{"time":567000,"text":"250 million years ago ..."},{"time":569000,"text":"... and then a catastrophe happened."},{"time":572000,"text":"And what happens next is the age of dinosaurs."},{"time":574000,"text":"It was all a mistake; it should have never happened. But it did."},{"time":578000,"text":"Now, luckily,"},{"time":580000,"text":"this Thrinaxodon, the size of a robin egg here:"},{"time":583000,"text":"this is a skull I've discovered just before taking this picture --"},{"time":586000,"text":"there's a pen for scale; it's really tiny --"},{"time":588000,"text":"this is in the Lower Triassic, after the mass extinction has finished."},{"time":592000,"text":"You can see the eye socket and you can see the little teeth in the front."},{"time":595000,"text":"If that does not survive, I'm not the thing giving this talk."},{"time":600000,"text":"Something else is, because if that doesn't survive, we are not here;"},{"time":604000,"text":"there are no mammals. It's that close; one species ekes through."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608000,"text":"Well, can we say anything about the pattern of who survives and who doesn't?"},{"time":611000,"text":"Here's sort of the end of that 10 years of work."},{"time":613000,"text":"The ranges of stuff -- the red line is the mass extinction."},{"time":616000,"text":"But we've got survivors and things that get through,"},{"time":618000,"text":"and it turns out the things that get through preferentially are cold bloods."},{"time":622000,"text":"Warm-blooded animals take a huge hit at this time."},{"time":627000,"text":"The survivors that do get through \n"},{"time":629000,"text":"produce this world of crocodile-like creatures."},{"time":632000,"text":"There's no dinosaurs yet; just this slow, saurian, scaly, nasty,"},{"time":636000,"text":"swampy place with a couple of tiny mammals hiding in the fringes."},{"time":641000,"text":"And there they would hide for 160 million years,"},{"time":644000,"text":"until liberated by that K-T asteroid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"So, if not impact, what?"},{"time":649000,"text":"And the what, I think, is that we returned, over and over again,"},{"time":653000,"text":"to the Pre-Cambrian world, that first microbial age,"},{"time":656000,"text":"and the microbes are still out there."},{"time":658000,"text":"They hate we animals."},{"time":660000,"text":"They really want their world back."},{"time":662000,"text":"And they've tried over and over and over again."},{"time":666000,"text":"This suggests to me that life causing these mass extinctions"},{"time":669000,"text":"because it did is inherently anti-Gaian."},{"time":672000,"text":"This whole Gaia idea, that life makes the world better for itself --"},{"time":677000,"text":"anybody been on a freeway on a Friday afternoon in Los Angeles"},{"time":681000,"text":"believing in the Gaia theory? No."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"So, I really suspect there's an alternative,"},{"time":686000,"text":"and that life does actually try to do itself in --"},{"time":688000,"text":"not consciously, but just because it does."},{"time":690000,"text":"And here's the weapon, it seems, that it did so over the last 500 million years."},{"time":694000,"text":"There are microbes which, through their metabolism,"},{"time":697000,"text":"produce hydrogen sulfide,"},{"time":699000,"text":"and they do so in large amounts."},{"time":702000,"text":"Hydrogen sulfide is very fatal to we humans."},{"time":705000,"text":"As small as 200 parts per million will kill you."},{"time":711000,"text":"You only have to go to the Black Sea and a few other places -- some lakes --"},{"time":715000,"text":"and get down, and you'll find that the water itself turns purple."},{"time":719000,"text":"It turns purple from the presence of numerous microbes"},{"time":722000,"text":"which have to have sunlight and have to have hydrogen sulfide,"},{"time":725000,"text":"and we can detect their presence today -- we can see them --"},{"time":729000,"text":"but we can also detect their presence in the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731000,"text":"And the last three years have seen"},{"time":733000,"text":"an enormous breakthrough in a brand-new field."},{"time":736000,"text":"I am almost extinct --"},{"time":738000,"text":"I'm a paleontologist who collects fossils."},{"time":740000,"text":"But the new wave of paleontologists -- my graduate students --"},{"time":743000,"text":"collect biomarkers."},{"time":745000,"text":"They take the sediment itself, they extract the oil from it, \n"},{"time":749000,"text":"and from that they can produce compounds"},{"time":751000,"text":"which turn out to be very specific to particular microbial groups."},{"time":755000,"text":"It's because lipids are so tough, they can get preserved in sediment"},{"time":759000,"text":"and last the hundreds of millions of years necessary,"},{"time":762000,"text":"and be extracted and tell us who was there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"And we know who was there. At the end of the Permian,"},{"time":767000,"text":"at many of these mass extinction boundaries,"},{"time":769000,"text":"this is what we find: isorenieratene. It's very specific."},{"time":773000,"text":"It can only occur if the surface of the ocean has no oxygen,"},{"time":777000,"text":"and is totally saturated with hydrogen sulfide --"},{"time":780000,"text":"enough, for instance, to come out of solution."},{"time":783000,"text":"This led Lee Kump, and others from Penn State and my group,"},{"time":787000,"text":"to propose what I call the Kump Hypothesis:"},{"time":790000,"text":"many of the mass extinctions were caused by lowering oxygen,"},{"time":793000,"text":"by high CO2. And the worst effect of global warming, it turns out:"},{"time":797000,"text":"hydrogen sulfide being produced out of the oceans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800000,"text":"Well, what's the source of this?"},{"time":802000,"text":"In this particular case, the source over and over has been flood basalts."},{"time":806000,"text":"This is a view of the Earth now, if we extract a lot of it."},{"time":809000,"text":"And each of these looks like a hydrogen bomb;"},{"time":811000,"text":"actually, the effects are even worse."},{"time":813000,"text":"This is when deep-Earth material comes to the surface,"},{"time":816000,"text":"spreads out over the surface of the planet."},{"time":818000,"text":"Well, it's not the lava that kills anything,"},{"time":821000,"text":"it's the carbon dioxide that comes out with it."},{"time":823000,"text":"This isn't Volvos; this is volcanoes."},{"time":826000,"text":"But carbon dioxide is carbon dioxide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829000,"text":"So, these are new data Rob Berner and I -- from Yale -- put together,"},{"time":832000,"text":"and what we try to do now is"},{"time":834000,"text":"track the amount of carbon dioxide in the entire rock record -- \n"},{"time":837000,"text":"and we can do this from a variety of means --"},{"time":840000,"text":"and put all the red lines here,"},{"time":842000,"text":"when these -- what I call greenhouse mass extinctions -- took place."},{"time":845000,"text":"And there's two things that are really evident here to me,"},{"time":847000,"text":"is that these extinctions take place when CO2 is going up."},{"time":850000,"text":"But the second thing that's not shown on here:"},{"time":853000,"text":"the Earth has never had any ice on it"},{"time":856000,"text":"when we've had 1,000 parts per million CO2."},{"time":860000,"text":"We are at 380 and climbing."},{"time":862000,"text":"We should be up to a thousand in three centuries at the most,"},{"time":865000,"text":"but my friend David Battisti in Seattle says he thinks a 100 years."},{"time":869000,"text":"So, there goes the ice caps,"},{"time":871000,"text":"and there comes 240 feet of sea level rise."},{"time":875000,"text":"I live in a view house now;"},{"time":877000,"text":"I'm going to have waterfront."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"All right, what's the consequence? The oceans probably turn purple."},{"time":883000,"text":"And we think this is the reason that complexity took so long"},{"time":886000,"text":"to take place on planet Earth."},{"time":888000,"text":"We had these hydrogen sulfide oceans for a very great long period."},{"time":891000,"text":"They stop complex life from existing."},{"time":895000,"text":"We know hydrogen sulfide is erupting presently a few places on the planet."},{"time":900000,"text":"And I throw this slide in -- this is me, actually, two months ago --"},{"time":904000,"text":"and I throw this slide in because here is my favorite animal, chambered nautilus."},{"time":908000,"text":"It's been on this planet since the animals first started -- 500 million years."},{"time":912000,"text":"This is a tracking experiment, and any of you scuba divers,"},{"time":915000,"text":"if you want to get involved in one of the coolest projects ever,"},{"time":918000,"text":"this is off the Great Barrier Reef."},{"time":920000,"text":"And as we speak now, \n"},{"time":921000,"text":"these nautilus are tracking out their behaviors to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924000,"text":"But the thing about this is that every once in a while"},{"time":928000,"text":"we divers can run into trouble,"},{"time":930000,"text":"so I'm going to do a little thought experiment here."},{"time":932000,"text":"This is a Great White Shark that ate some of my traps."},{"time":935000,"text":"We pulled it up; up it comes. So, it's out there with me at night."},{"time":938000,"text":"So, I'm swimming along, and it takes off my leg."},{"time":941000,"text":"I'm 80 miles from shore, what's going to happen to me?"},{"time":944000,"text":"Well now, I die."},{"time":946000,"text":"Five years from now, this is what I hope happens to me:"},{"time":948000,"text":"I'm taken back to the boat, I'm given a gas mask:"},{"time":951000,"text":"80 parts per million hydrogen sulfide."},{"time":954000,"text":"I'm then thrown in an ice pond, I'm cooled 15 degrees lower"},{"time":958000,"text":"and I could be taken to a critical care hospital."},{"time":962000,"text":"And the reason I could do that is because we mammals"},{"time":964000,"text":"have gone through a series of these hydrogen sulfide events,"},{"time":967000,"text":"and our bodies have adapted."},{"time":969000,"text":"And we can now use this as what I think will be a major medical breakthrough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":973000,"text":"This is Mark Roth. He was funded by DARPA."},{"time":975000,"text":"Tried to figure out how to save Americans after battlefield injuries."},{"time":979000,"text":"He bleeds out pigs."},{"time":981000,"text":"He puts in 80 parts per million hydrogen sulfide --"},{"time":984000,"text":"the same stuff that survived these past mass extinctions --"},{"time":987000,"text":"and he turns a mammal into a reptile."},{"time":989000,"text":"\"I believe we are seeing in this response the result of mammals and reptiles"},{"time":993000,"text":"having undergone a series of exposures to H2S.\""},{"time":996000,"text":"I got this email from him two years ago;"},{"time":998000,"text":"he said, \"I think I've got an answer to some of your questions.\""},{"time":1001000,"text":"So, he now has taken mice down"},{"time":1003000,"text":"for as many as four hours, sometimes six hours,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"and these are brand-new data he sent me on the way over here."},{"time":1009000,"text":"On the top, now, that is a temperature record of a mouse who has gone through --"},{"time":1014000,"text":"the dotted line, the temperatures."},{"time":1016000,"text":"So, the temperature starts at 25 centigrade,"},{"time":1018000,"text":"and down it goes, down it goes."},{"time":1019000,"text":"Six hours later, up goes the temperature."},{"time":1021000,"text":"Now, the same mouse is given 80 parts per million hydrogen sulfide"},{"time":1026000,"text":"in this solid graph,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"and look what happens to its temperature."},{"time":1030000,"text":"Its temperature drops."},{"time":1032000,"text":"It goes down to 15 degrees centigrade from 35,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"and comes out of this perfectly fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039000,"text":"Here is a way we can get people to critical care."},{"time":1042000,"text":"Here's how we can bring people cold enough to last till we get critical care."},{"time":1048000,"text":"Now, you're all thinking, yeah, what about the brain tissue?"},{"time":1052000,"text":"And so this is one of the great challenges that is going to happen."},{"time":1055000,"text":"You're in an accident. You've got two choices:"},{"time":1057000,"text":"you're going to die, or you're going to take the hydrogen sulfide"},{"time":1060000,"text":"and, say, 75 percent of you is saved, mentally."},{"time":1063000,"text":"What are you going to do?"},{"time":1065000,"text":"Do we all have to have a little button saying, Let me die?"},{"time":1068000,"text":"This is coming towards us,"},{"time":1070000,"text":"and I think this is going to be a revolution."},{"time":1072000,"text":"We're going to save lives, but there's going to be a cost to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075000,"text":"The new view of mass extinctions is, yes, we were hit,"},{"time":1077000,"text":"and, yes, we have to think about the long term,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"because we will get hit again."},{"time":1081000,"text":"But there's a far worse danger confronting us."},{"time":1083000,"text":"We can easily go back to the hydrogen sulfide world."},{"time":1086000,"text":"Give us a few millennia --"},{"time":1088000,"text":"and we humans should last those few millennia --"},{"time":1090000,"text":"will it happen again? If we continue, it'll happen again."},{"time":1094000,"text":"How many of us flew here?"},{"time":1096000,"text":"How many of us have gone through"},{"time":1098000,"text":"our entire Kyoto quota"},{"time":1101000,"text":"just for flying this year?"},{"time":1103000,"text":"How many of you have exceeded it? Yeah, I've certainly exceeded it."},{"time":1106000,"text":"We have a huge problem facing us as a species."},{"time":1109000,"text":"We have to beat this."},{"time":1111000,"text":"I want to be able to go back to this reef. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1121000,"text":"Chris Anderson: I've just got one question for you, Peter."},{"time":1123000,"text":"Am I understanding you right, that what you're saying here"},{"time":1125000,"text":"is that we have in our own bodies"},{"time":1127000,"text":"a biochemical response to hydrogen sulfide"},{"time":1131000,"text":"that in your mind proves that there have been past mass extinctions"},{"time":1134000,"text":"due to climate change?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1136000,"text":"Peter Ward: Yeah, every single cell in us"},{"time":1138000,"text":"can produce minute quantities of hydrogen sulfide in great crises."},{"time":1142000,"text":"This is what Roth has found out."},{"time":1143000,"text":"So, what we're looking at now: does it leave a signal?"},{"time":1145000,"text":"Does it leave a signal in bone or in plant?"},{"time":1147000,"text":"And we go back to the fossil record and we could try to detect"},{"time":1150000,"text":"how many of these have happened in the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1152000,"text":"CA: It's simultaneously"},{"time":1154000,"text":"an incredible medical technique, but also a terrifying ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1157000,"text":"PW: Blessing and curse."}]}]}